{
  "doc_id": "50325",
  "text": "Cell culture and virus strains. Chick kidneys were prepared from 2 to 3 week old specific pathogen free (SPF) Rhode Island Red chickens. Primary chick kidney cells (CK cells) were prepared as described previously [CITATION_1] . DF1 cells [CITATION_2] were maintained in 1x DMEM (Sigma) supplemented with 10% FCS and 100U Pen/Strep. IBV Beau-R is an apathogenic molecular clone of Beaudette-CK described previously [CITATION_3] . M4-CK is a pathogenic strain of IBV adapted to grow in CK cells, here referred to as M41 [CITATION_4] .",
